2008", shape=ellipse, fillcolor="#e8f0ff", tooltip="This document specifies a new resource record (RR) for the Domain Name System (DNS), and how to use it with the Host Identity Protocol (HIP).  This RR allows a HIP node to store in the DNS its Host Identity (HI, the public component of the node public-private key pair), Host Identity Tag (HIT, a truncated hash of its public key), and the Domain Names of its rendezvous servers (RVSs).  This memo defines an Experimental Protocol for the Internet community."]; 

